---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BreadcrumbSchema from '../components/schema/BreadcrumbSchema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Perfume Picks privacy policy — what data we collect, how it is used, and how to delete your account."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <BreadcrumbSchema crumbs={[{ name: 'Privacy Policy', url: `${SITE.url}/privacy` }]} />
  </Fragment>

  <p class="brand">{SITE.name}</p>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="effective">Effective Date: May 13, 2026</p>

  <p>
    Perfume Picks ("we", "our", or "the app") is a fragrance wardrobe and
    wear-log app for iOS, with a companion website at
    <a href={SITE.url}>{SITE.url}</a>. This policy explains what we collect,
    how we use it, and how to delete it &mdash; for both the app and the website.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Account information.</strong> If you sign in with Apple or Google,
    we receive your email and a unique identifier from the provider. Guest
    accounts store only an anonymous identifier with no personal information.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>User-generated content.</strong> Wardrobe entries, wear logs,
    ratings, swipe feedback, quiz responses, taste-profile data, private notes,
    and SOTD posts are stored in your account.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Device data.</strong> A device identifier and basic diagnostics
    (OS version, device model, app version) are collected to deliver core
    features and prevent abuse. We do not collect precise location.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Purchase information.</strong> Subscription transactions are
    processed by Apple through the App Store and by RevenueCat as the
    subscription manager. We receive a purchase confirmation but never see
    your payment details.
  </p>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To run your wardrobe, wear log, and taste profile.</li>
    <li>To suggest fragrances you already own based on weather, occasion, and recent wears.</li>
    <li>To sync your wardrobe and wear history across devices.</li>
    <li>To improve our taste-profile model using anonymized swipe and wear data.</li>
    <li>To process subscription payments through the App Store via RevenueCat.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Privacy Posture</h2>
  <p>
    Your wardrobe, wear log, ratings, private notes, and taste profile are
    <strong>private by default</strong>. Scent of the Day posts become public
    only when you explicitly toggle that entry public. We do not run cross-user
    advertising, and we do not sell personal information.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    We rely on the following third parties to operate the app. Each receives
    only the data necessary for the service it provides:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Supabase</strong> &mdash; backend storage and authentication.</li>
    <li><strong>RevenueCat</strong> &mdash; subscription management.</li>
    <li><strong>Apple / Google</strong> &mdash; sign-in and payment processing.</li>
    <li><strong>PostHog</strong> &mdash; anonymous usage analytics.</li>
    <li><strong>Sentry</strong> &mdash; anonymous crash reporting.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Affiliate Link Tracking</h2>
  <p>
    When a fragrance detail page links out to a retailer such as FragranceX,
    Sephora, or Amazon Luxury Beauty, the retailer may set cookies or
    identifiers on the destination site that we have no control over. Perfume
    Picks itself only records that an outbound click occurred &mdash; we do
    not pass your account identity to the retailer.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Your data is retained as long as your account is active. You may delete
    your account at any time from the Profile screen, which permanently
    removes all associated data including wardrobe entries, wear logs, swipe
    history, quiz results, taste profile, ratings, private notes, and SOTD
    posts.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>
    You may request a copy of your data, request correction or deletion, and
    withdraw consent at any time. California residents and EU users have
    additional rights under CCPA and GDPR respectively. Contact us using the
    address below.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Perfume Picks is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly
    collect information from anyone under 13.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Data Security</h2>
  <p>
    All data is transmitted over HTTPS and stored in secured, access-controlled
    databases. Authentication tokens are stored securely on your device. We
    follow industry-standard practices to protect your information.
  </p>

  <h2>10. How to Delete Your Account</h2>
  <p>You may delete your account in two ways:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>In-app:</strong> Profile &rarr; Settings &rarr; Delete Account.</li>
    <li><strong>By email:</strong> if you cannot access the app, email
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a> from
      your account email with the subject <strong>"Delete My Account"</strong>.
      We will permanently remove your account within 7 days.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be
    communicated through the app. Continued use after changes constitutes
    acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For questions about this privacy policy or your data, contact us at:
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>
  </p>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
